-- Dutch-based property firm Domus to sell up to $281 mln of shares in IPO
-- By Freya Berry
-- Thu Apr 24, 2014 03:33AM EDT
-- None



LONDON, April 24 (Reuters) - Netherlands-based property firm Domus [IPO-DMS.AX] and its parent company are to sell up to 250.16 million euros ($345.96 million) of new and existing shares in an Amsterdam listing.

RPG Byty, which fully owns Domus, said on Thursday that the price for Domus's IPO had been set 16.50-20.50 euros per share. RPG will sell 9.9 mln existing shares, equal to 55 percent of current issued capital, while Domus will raise around 38 million euros in new shares.